The paper discusses the spread of malware through WiFi networks, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of an epidemiological model to simulate the spread of the contagion suggests a focus on complex systems (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the mention of computational estimates and percolation thresholds suggests a possible connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
